1.how to create a file---->
  1.cat >> <filename>
  2.touch <f1> <f2>
  3.vim <f1>
  4.nano <f1>

  -------for the diffrentiation of above commands read blog for basic followed to advanced linux-----

2.Make directory=folder---->"mkdir"   <-----multiple directories also created follwed by name

3.change directory ==> cd <directory name> or "cd .." <----for reverse 

4.to check present directory---->pwd
5.copy----> cp file1 file2 
6.move---->  mv file1 file2
7.for listing present dir or files---->ls or ls-a(for hidden files)
8. to create hidden files with any above command = touch .filename


9.for delteion of file multiple commands are used depending upon the type of file or data present in the file--------
 1.rmdir <directory name> = for empty dir
 2.rmdir -p dir1/dir2 =for parent child or sub child deltion
 3.rmdir -pv 
 4.rm -rf = remove non file or directory
 

10. history----> list of no. of commands run by user

                                

 important commands--->

1. lsb_release -a --->name of your machine
2.hostname--->name of  your server
3.ifconfig----> to view ip adress.....install net-tools first 
4.sudo su ---->switch user do --to increase the functionality of your machine
5.apt install <pkg name> ---> to install downloaded software on your machine
   apt install git---> for git installation

6.which <pkg or filename> ------> to find where is your file or pakage is located
  which git

7.wget <downloaded link> ----> to download something from internet-----first download and then install it
8.whoami --->user name 

9.echo ----> to print something on your screen 
10. grep ---->to find any word or file
11. sort--->for sorting of file

12. tree----> this is used for tree like reprenstation of data...you need to first install it then use it


for basic to high ---->

1.useradd <username> ----> to create user  in your machine
2.groupadd <groupname> ---->to add group 
3. gpasswd -a <username> <groupname> ----> to add  single user in your group
  gpasswd -M <u1> <u2> <groupname> ------> to add multiple user in your group
  cat /etc/group----> to see the list of member in a group

4. ln -s <filename> ----> to create a soft link of your file in a desktop
   ln <f1> <f2> -----> to create a backup file for the original  file
 
5. tar -cvf dir1.tar dir1 ------------> to combine all files in one just like zipping up the file

6. gzip dir1.tar -------> to compress the the file
7. gunzip dir1.tar.gz ----> to decomprss
8. tar -xvf file1.tar----> to unzip



  --ownership of file and directories

1.chmod 777 <file or directory name> ------> to give read, write and execute permission to your user
2. chown < user> <filename> ----->to transfer the ownership from root to user
3.chgrp <groupname> <filename> ----->to change the group



4. 1.vim <filename>.sh ----> to run multi command in one click make them in .sh  file
   2. --> ./filename --->by running this all command will execute in sorted order
